Hungarian lawmakers lifted a local
 tax exemption  for Budapest Airport Zrt., in which  Hochtief AG (HOT) 
holds a 50 percent stake, news website Origo reported without
citing anyone.  The motion, which will force the airport operator to pay at
least 1 billion forint ($4.6 million) in property taxes, was
supported by Prime Minister  Viktor Orban  and the leadership of
the ruling Fidesz party, according to Origo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
